# 🔗 URL Shortener (Node.js + Express + MongoDB)

A production-inspired URL shortener with **JWT authentication, role-based access (Admin/User), analytics, custom aliases, and link expiry**.

## ✨ Features

* 🔐 **Authentication (JWT + cookies)**
* 👤 **User-specific URLs**
* 👑 **Admin dashboard**
* ✏️ **Custom short aliases**
* ⏳ **Link expiry (time-based)**
* 📊 **Basic analytics (click count + timestamps)**
* 🚫 **Rate limiting (anti-spam)**
* 🧼 **Input validation (Joi)**
* 🎯 **Clean MVC architecture**

## 🧱 Tech Stack

* Backend: Node.js, Express
* DB: MongoDB (Mongoose)
* Auth: JWT + Cookies
* Views: EJS
* Validation: Joi

## 🗂️ Folder Structure

```
src/
├── controllers/
├── routes/
├── middleware/
├── models/
├── services/
├── validators/
└── index.js
views/
```

## ⚙️ Setup

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Arjun-explores-Arjun-learn/url-shortener-nodejs.git
cd url-shortener-nodejs
npm install
```

Create `.env`:

```
PORT=7001
MONGO_URL=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/url-shortener
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
```

Run:

```bash
npm start
```

## 🔌 API Endpoints (core)

* `POST /user/signup`
* `POST /user/login`
* `POST /url` → create short URL
* `GET /:shortId` → redirect
* `GET /url/analytics/:shortId` → analytics
* `GET /admin/urls` → admin dashboard (protected)

